<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>LaMott George Bates was born at Richfield, Summit Co., Ohio, October 13, 1847. About 1852, he moved with his parent to Oberlin, Ohio; then in 1855, the family moved to a plot of land in Fairfield Township in Shiawassee County, about three miles northeast of what became the village of Elsie. Bates returned for a time to Richfield staying with an aunt, and there learned the harness trade.  Around 1867, he returned to Elsie, where he joined his father in a harness shop operation. In 1872, L. G. Bates joined with J. F. Hasty, who owned a cooperage, and together they opened a mercantile business. In 1873, Bates married Hannah Amanda Sickels also of Elsie, Michigan. In 1877, having left the partnership with Hasty some years before, Bates accepted Hasty's offer to renew the partnership. Bates accepted, then a year later, bought Hasty's interest in the store, renaming it under his own name, L. G. Bates.</p>
</bioghist>



<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The record group consists of financial records detailing the operation of the L. G. Bates General Store and its predecessor firm, J. F. Hasty and Co. As the dates of some of the records precede the opening of the Hasty store, it is possible that some of the accounts and ledgers are of a Sickel family member. In addition, the collection includes family correspondence, diaries and notebooks probably of Bates, family history and genealogy, photographs, and printed material.</p>
</scopecontent>

